The paper deals with natural language processing, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a novel algorithm for learning the parameters of the model, which involves stochastic sampling and locality-sensitive hashing, indicating a potential overlap with "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) and "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) subcategories. The paper also mentions a real-world problem of extracting biological models from scientific papers, which suggests a possible connection to "Information Retrieval" (cs.IR) and "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI) subcategories.
